result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexis N Dukes was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Alexis N Dukes in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
The Defendant was sentenced as follows:
FINE: $389.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid at $25.00 per month commencing 8/1/16 or serve 10 days jail consecutive as penalty for payment).
DNA SURCHARGE $200.00 (to be paid at $25.00 per month consecutive to payment on fine).
  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Community Service: Defendant is required to perform 20 Hours Community Service within 1 year to be monitored by WCS.  Court authorizes credit towards costs/fine to be at the rate of $10.00/hour.  Adjustment will be made upon proof of completion.
